The '''Dressellian Projectile Rifle''' was a [[Slugthrower rifle/Legends|slugthrower rifle]] used by the [[Dressellian/Legends|Dressellians]] in their [[Dressellian resistance|resistance]] against the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire's]] occupation of their [[Homeworld/Legends|homeworld]], [[Dressel/Legends|Dressel]]. A crude [[Weapon/Legends|weapon]] typically built with primitive tools, some of the [[Slugthrower/Legends|slugthrowers]] were made by the Dressellians, while others were [[Smuggler/Legends|smuggled]] to Dressel by [[Bothan/Legends|Bothans]]. In [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]], several Dressellians fought for the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]] at the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]], and the Dressellian Projectile Rifle was among the weapons used by the [[Species/Legends|species]] in the battle.

==Description==
Manufactured by members of the [[Dressellian/Legends|Dressellian]] or [[Bothan/Legends|Bothan]] [[Species/Legends|species]], the Dressellian Projectile Rifle was made of the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Dressel/Legends|Dressel's]] native [[Wood/Legends|woods]] along with easily smelted metals. The [[Slugthrower rifle/Legends|slugthrower rifle]] was medium-sized, weighed four [[Kilogram/Legends|kilograms]], and cost 300 [[Galactic Credit Standard/Legends|credits]].<ref name="Ultimate Alien Anthology" /> Capable of firing to a range of 200 [[Meter/Legends|meters]],<ref name="Arms note" /> the [[Rifle/Legends|rifle]] had a clip of twelve piercing shots and a multifire capability.<ref name="Ultimate Alien Anthology" /> For the rifle's shells,<ref name="EGWT">''[[The Essential Guide to Weapons and Technology]]''</ref> replacement twelve-round clips cost five credits each.<ref name="Ultimate Alien Anthology" />

The rifle included a long [[Barrel/Legends|barrel]] with a [[Scope/Legends|scope]], a cartridge loader, trigger, large [[Stock/Legends|stock]], and a carry strap.<ref name="EGWT" /> [[Color/Legends|Colored]] brown, the [[Weapon/Legends|weapon's]] scope, strap, cartridge loader, and trigger were black. The rifle also had a black ring above the strap as well as between the barrel and scope.<ref name="PotF">{{KennerCite|set=Star Wars: The Power of the Force (1995 toy line)|pack=Orrimaarko (Prune Face)|link=POTF2pruneface.asp}}</ref> It was a crude weapon that was normally hand-built with primitive tools.<ref name="EGWT" /> Typical of projectile weapons built by native species, the Dressellian Projectile Rifle was similar to the [[Tusken Raider/Legends|Tusken Raider]] species' [[Cycler rifle/Legends|Tusken Cycler rifles]].<ref name="Ultimate Alien Anthology" />

==History==
[[File:Dressellian_rifle.png|thumb|right|280px|A Dressellian serving the Alliance to Restore the Republic carrying a Dressellian Projectile Rifle]]
During the [[Dressellian resistance]] against the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]], their projectile rifles were among the weapons used to drive off the Imperial presence on their [[Homeworld/Legends|homeworld]]. With some of the rifles made by Dressellians, others were [[Smuggler/Legends|smuggled]] to their world by the Bothan species.<ref name="Ultimate Alien Anthology" /> The Bothans were able to conceal their involvement, as their aid to the Dressellians was limited to delivering [[Slugthrower/Legends|slugthrower]] rifles.<ref name="EGWT" /> Overall, the Dressellian Projectile Rifle was an excellent example of slugthrower rifles produced by low-technology societies.<ref name="Ultimate Alien Anthology" />

By [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]],<ref name="Galactic Files">{{Topps|set=2013 Topps Star Wars Galactic Files Series 2|cardname=#530 - Orrimaarko|link=https://www.tcdb.com/ViewCard.cfm/sid/93283/cid/6569556/2013-Topps-Star-Wars-Galactic-Files-Series-2-530-Orrimaarko}}</ref> several Dressellians joined the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]] and participated in the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]].<ref name="EGWT" /> The former Dressellian resistance fighter [[Orrimaarko/Legends|Orrimaarko]] participated in the Battle of Endor,<ref name="Galactic Files" /> using their species' Projectile Rifles around that [[Time/Legends|time]].<ref name="toy" /><ref name="ROTJ">{{Film|VI}}</ref> The battle ended with an Alliance victory over the Empire.<ref name="ROTJ" />

==Behind the scenes==
The Dressellian Projectile Rifle first appeared in [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Star Wars'': Episode VI ''Return of the Jedi'']], the [[1983]] third film of the [[original trilogy]]. It was held by a Dressellian aboard the [[MC80A Home One Type Heavy Star Cruiser/Legends|MC80 ''Home One'' type Star Cruiser]] [[Home One/Legends|''Home One'']],<ref name="ROTJ" /> with all of the scenes aboard the [[MC80 Star Cruiser/Legends|cruiser]] filmed throughout the week of Tuesday, [[February 16]], [[1982]].<ref name="BTS">{{WebCite|url=https://swnz.co.nz/2017/03/11/gerald-home-tessek-squid-head-mon-calamari-officer-2|text=Gerald Home as Tessek (Squid Head) and Mon Calamari Officer|author=G., Matt|date=2004-06-11|work=[https://swnz.co.nz Star Wars New Zealand]|archiveurl=https://archive.vn/JbkiZ}}</ref> In [[1997]], the rifle was first named as the "Dresselian projectile rifle" in ''[[The Essential Guide to Weapons and Technology]]''<ref name="EGWT" /> before [[2002]]'s ''[[Arms & Equipment Guide]]'' capitalized it as the "Dresselian Projectile Rifle."<ref name="Arms">''[[Arms & Equipment Guide]]''</ref> [[2003]]'s ''[[Ultimate Alien Anthology]]'' identified it as the Dressellian Projectile Rifle.<ref name="Ultimate Alien Anthology" /> While the [[2011]] ''[[Star Wars: Head-to-Head Tag Teams]]'' once more referred to the weapon as the "Dresselian projectile rifle,"<ref name="HH">''[[Star Wars: Head-to-Head Tag Teams]]''</ref> and the [[2013]] [[Star Wars: Edge of the Empire Core Rulebook|''Star Wars: Edge of the Empire'' Core Rulebook]] repeated the "Dresselian Projectile Rifle" identification,<ref name="Edge">[[Star Wars: Edge of the Empire Core Rulebook|''Star Wars: Edge of the Empire'' Core Rulebook]]</ref> this article treats "Dressellian Projectile Rifle" as the proper name<ref name="Ultimate Alien Anthology" /> as it matches the species' name's spelling with the double "l."<ref name="db">{{DB|character|orrimaarko|Orrimaarko}}</ref>

[[File:Vintprunefacerifle.jpg|thumb|left|280px|A Dressellian Projectile Rifle's appearance for the Kenner ''Star Wars: Return of the Jedi'' toy line]]
A number of other inconsistencies exist with the rifle. ''The Essential Guide to Weapons and Technology'' lists the weapon's maximum range as 300 meters, with an optimum range of 150 meters, while listing it as carrying six shells in its clip.<ref name="EGWT" /> This is contradicted by ''Arms & Eqipment Guide'' and ''Ultimate Alien Anthology'', which list the two 200 meter range and twelve-shell statistics that are presented in this article.<ref name="Ultimate Alien Anthology" /><ref name="Arms" /> The rifle's appearance is also inconsistent. While the way this article describes its appearance is matching with the prop's design,<ref name="PotF" /><ref name="SWE">''[[Star Wars Encyclopedia]]''</ref> Orrimaarko's figure for the [[1984]] [[Kenner Products]] [[Star Wars: Return of the Jedi (toy line)|''Star Wars: Return of the Jedi'' toy line]] showed the entire rifle as brown,<ref name="toy" /> and his [[2012]] ''[[Star Wars: The Vintage Collection]]'' figure does not include the black ring between the barrel and scope or above the carry strap.<ref name="Vintage Collection">{{HasbroCite|set=Star Wars: The Vintage Collection|pack=#114: Orrimaarko (Prune Face)|altlink=https://www.rebelscum.com/Orrimaarko_Prune_Face_Vintage_Collection_TVC_VC114.asp}}</ref>

